\vspace{0.5in}
We notice contradictory statements of Z.Ahmed on $\mathcal{PT}$-symmetry 
potential $V(x)=\frac{x^{2}}{4}+igx|x|$ (g=2) .The curve (dash-dot) shows only
one zero ,whose corresponding energy eigenvalue is 1.72. This graphical 
representation contradicts the discussion (presented below the graph),which
 claims number of real discrete states between $0.4 \leq g \leq 2.3$ are 3.
As g=2  $ <$ g=2.3 ,one should get number of real discrete states  3
 instad of 1.
However, present calculation using matrix diagonalisation method reflects  3
.Secondly the statement on complex Harmonic oscillator $V_{H}=x^{2}+ix$
(which entails complete real discrete spectrum), as a singular example is not 
acceptable ,as we notice many complex $\mathcal{PT}$ symmetric potentials 
can be constructed ,which would reflect infinite real discrete energy eigenvalues. 

